		{
			"id": "hm4sY0r8",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -40.87310984112446,
			"y": 5771.872121764303,
			"width": 908.143310546875,
			"height": 40,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1971c2",
			"backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "dashed",
			"roughness": 2,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "b2g",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 1339954830,
			"version": 585,
			"versionNonce": 950737307,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1761025370620,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "To acheive same functionality in other data bases we use zookeeper . that manages this with help of primary nodes\n.With there is not single point of failure in cassandra  . like in other system we have. ",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "To acheive same functionality in other data bases we use zookeeper . that manages this with help of primary nodes\n.With there is not single point of failure in cassandra  . like in other system we have. ",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"id": "YN4Mgya9",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -426.2496574912102,
			"y": 5734.428192111335,
			"width": 183.7438507080078,
			"height": 80,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1971c2",
			"backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "dashed",
			"roughness": 2,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "b2h",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 1773631506,
			"version": 414,
			"versionNonce": 1300039957,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1761023581613,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "Cap Theorem \n    C: consistency\n    A: Availability\n    P: partion Tolerance",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "Cap Theorem \n    C: consistency\n    A: Availability\n    P: partion Tolerance",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"id": "REeYvUXB",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -408.7496574912102,
			"y": 5843.914581271491,
			"width": 970.990966796875,
			"height": 80,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1971c2",
			"backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "dashed",
			"roughness": 2,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "b2j",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 565278350,
			"version": 917,
			"versionNonce": 1870995061,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1761023581613,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "According to cap theorem u have to choose to factor . Cassandra only support Availability and Partition tolerance . \nas there no master node the consistency is not guaranteed .\nWith Gossip protocal it takes time for nodes to come on eventual consistency . if request comes in that time and node are \nnot synced it will give u older data.  ",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "According to cap theorem u have to choose to factor . Cassandra only support Availability and Partition tolerance . \nas there no master node the consistency is not guaranteed .\nWith Gossip protocal it takes time for nodes to come on eventual consistency . if request comes in that time and node are \nnot synced it will give u older data.  ",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
		{
			"id": "Nz4ZMSAL",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -413.5006340537102,
			"y": 5970.662628146491,
			"width": 526.8795166015625,
			"height": 80,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1971c2",
			"backgroundColor": "#ffec99",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 1,
			"strokeStyle": "dashed",
			"roughness": 2,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "b2l",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 764417934,
			"version": 638,
			"versionNonce": 916686805,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1761023581613,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "tunable consistency per query\n    One waits for one replica - fastest ,but weakest consistency.\n    Quorum waits for a majority - a balanced middle ground.\n    ALL waits for every replica- strongest consistency, but slowest.",
			"fontSize": 16,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "tunable consistency per query\n    One waits for one replica - fastest ,but weakest consistency.\n    Quorum waits for a majority - a balanced middle ground.\n    ALL waits for every replica- strongest consistency, but slowest.",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"rawText": ""
		},
